---
const siteBase = Astro.site?.href?.replace(/\/$/, "") ?? "https://dome.dowi.es";
const privacyPolicyUrl = `${siteBase}/privacy/`;
---

<section class="app-purpose" id="about-dome" aria-labelledby="app-purpose-heading">
  <div class="app-purpose-inner">
    <h2 id="app-purpose-heading" class="app-purpose-title">What is Dome?</h2>
    <div class="app-purpose-body">
      <p>
        <strong>Dome</strong> is a desktop application (built with Electron) for
        <strong>knowledge management</strong> and <strong>academic research</strong>.
        It is designed for researchers, academics, and knowledge workers who need one
        place to organize notes, PDFs, presentations, videos, audio, images, and web
        articles in projects—and to work with them using AI.
      </p>
      <p>
        Dome includes an AI assistant (<strong>Many</strong>), reasoning-based
        document indexing for search, a Notion-style editor, PDF annotations, study
        tools (Studio, flashcards), calendar and optional cloud integrations. Your
        library stays on your device unless you choose to use online features or
        providers; see our <a href={privacyPolicyUrl}>Privacy Policy</a> for details.
      </p>

      <h3 class="app-purpose-subheading" id="google-data">
        Google account (optional)
      </h3>
      <p>
        If you choose to connect <strong>Google</strong>, Dome uses
        <strong>OAuth 2.0</strong> on your device for optional features only—for
        example, importing files from <strong>Google Drive</strong> and syncing
        events with <strong>Google Calendar</strong>. Access is granted only after
        you sign in with Google inside the app. OAuth tokens are stored
        <strong>locally</strong> on your machine (for example in Dome’s local
        database); they are <strong>not</strong> sent through Dome’s servers. You can
        disconnect these integrations at any time in the app settings. How Google
        processes data on its side is described in
        <a
          href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">Google’s Privacy Policy</a
        >. For a full breakdown, see our
        <a href={privacyPolicyUrl}>Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .app-purpose {
    padding: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 5rem) 40px;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .app-purpose-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .app-purpose-title {
    font-family: var(--font-cartel);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .app-purpose-subheading {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 1.75rem 0 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .app-purpose-body p {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .app-purpose-body p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .app-purpose-body strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .app-purpose-body a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .app-purpose-body a:hover {
    color: #4a502e;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .app-purpose {
      padding: 48px 20px;
    }

    .app-purpose-body p {
      font-size: 16px;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .app-purpose {
      padding: 40px 16px;
    }
  }
</style>
